{
  "texts": [
    "We account for the pandemic using a dummy variable (COVID) equal to one during the COVID-19 period (after the date of deflation on the pandemic on 03/11/2020 by the World Health Organization) and zero otherwise.",
    "To test efficiency in the Bitcoin and Ethereum markets, we follow Le Tran and Leirvik (2019) by estimating the daily AMIM values based on Eq.",
    "(6) using overlapping window data for one year.",
    "5 The results of the descriptive statistics for daily AMIM are presented in Table 2.",
    "They show that the mean values of AMIM are positive and statistically significant (suggested by small standard error values) for the two assets, indicating that both the Bitcoin and Ethereum markets are inefficient on average."
  ]
}